OL,5, The minimum wage set by the government,
OL,6, known as the national living wage, is  
OL,7, increasing by more than a pound for the
OL,8, first time, providing a welcome boost  
OL,9, for 2.7 million low-paid workers.      
OL,11,FThe main wage rate is rising from      
OL,12,F#10.42 to #11.44 an hour and will apply
OL,13,Fto workers over 21 rather than over 23.
OL,15,FYounger workers will also see a rise in
OL,16,Fthe rates that apply to them.          
OL,18,FHowever some businesses say the higher 
OL,19,Flabour costs will make it harder for   
OL,20,Fthem to keep prices down.              
